10/11/2008
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- The State Audit Institution (DRI) has unveiled numerous irregularities in the work of the defence ministry, Podgorica-based daily Vijesti reported on Sunday (November 9th). 
According to the newspaper, the irregularities include illegal benefits, improper spending and falsification of accounting documentation. 
The DRI inspection also found that last year the ministry spent 1.54m euros more than approved in the country's budget. 
(MIA, Vijesti - 09/11/08)
